''Today is Monday'', the 26th of September.
The weather is nice. I like the colours of the Indian summer.

We played cops and robbers today, the whole class, during the big break. "You filled the courtyard with life like never before. Everyone's been talking about it in the staff room." Ms. Cloels told us afterwards.

One time, I tried to catch |dp>[(link-goto: "Christine", "Dramatis Personae")], but she is bigger than me and faster. She doesn't turn her knees in awkwardly when she's running, like so many of the other girls.

|c1>[Finally, when I had managed to corner her...<br>]\
|c2>[I gave up chasing her...<br>]
---
(align: "==>")[|tp>[]]\
{
(click-replace: ?c1)[Finally, when I had managed to corner her, she said she wasn't playing any more. When I asked why she told me playing cops and robbers was childish.\
	{
	(replace: ?c2)[]\
	(replace: ?dp)[Christine]\
	(replace: ?tp)[(font: "Times New Roman")[(link-goto: "Continue the diary", "Entry 2A")]]\
	(set: $infatuation = $infatuation + $firstYearConstant)\
	(set: $confidence = $confidence - $firstYearConstant)\
	(set: $ChristineNotes to $ChristineNotes + (a: "Christine is very mature and doesn't play games like little children do."))\
	}
]\
(click-replace: ?c2)[I gave up chasing her and guarded the prison instead until the end of the break. I couldn't prevent a couple of escapes, though.\
	{
	(replace: ?c1)[]\
	(replace: ?dp)[Christine]\
	(replace: ?tp)[(font: "Times New Roman")[(link-goto: "Continue the diary", "Entry 2B")]]\
	(set: $friendship = $friendship + $firstYearConstant)\
	(set: $ChristineNotes to $ChristineNotes + (a: "Christine is very sporty. She's faster than many of the boys."))\
	}
]\
(unless: $visitedPassages contains (passage:)'s name)[
	{
	(set: $dramatisPersonae to $dramatisPersonae + (a: "|Christine>[Christine]"))\
	(set: $ChristineNotes to $ChristineNotes + (a: "I don't know much about her and I haven't really spoken to her either. Michael says she's in the basketball and drama clubs."))\
	}
]\
}

''Today is Wednesday'', the 7th of December.
The sky is grey. It's dark when I leave and as I return.

Mama and Papa took me to the concert hall yesterday. There was a screening of "The Gold Rush" by Charlie Chaplin. The music for this silent film was performed by a full philharmonic orchestra. I liked the film, it was funny. I also liked the music. Listening to a live orchestra performance is very different from listening to the radio or tape deck.

Today, in school, |dp>[(link-goto: "David", "Dramatis Personae")] told me about this computer programming thing he does. Apparently he wants to make a video game himself and has spent the last few days learning how to do it. He asked me what I did yesterday.

|c1>[I told him about the film at the concert hall...<br>]\
|c2>[I told him I went to the cinema...<br>]\
|c3>[]\
|c4>[]
